Add `getApifyRunStatus` and its supporting types to `packages/service-core/src/services/accommodation-import/adapters/apify-client.ts`.

```ts
export type ApifyRunStatus =
    | 'READY' | 'RUNNING' | 'SUCCEEDED' | 'FAILED' | 'TIMED-OUT' | 'ABORTED';

export interface GetApifyRunStatusResult {
    readonly status: ApifyRunStatus;
    readonly defaultDatasetId: string;
}

export async function getApifyRunStatus(input: {
    token: string;
    runId: string;
}): Promise<GetApifyRunStatusResult | null>
```

Implementation details:
- GET `https://api.apify.com/v2/actor-runs/{runId}` with `Authorization: Bearer {token}`.
- On 200: return `{ status: data.status, defaultDatasetId: data.defaultDatasetId }` with defensive checks (return null if missing).
- On any non-2xx or fetch error: return `null`. Never throws.

